      <section eId="sec_CCP-3031">
        <num>CCP 3031</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3031__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>When a testament has been probated or given the effect of probate, and subject to the provisions of Article 3033, the court may send all of the legatees into possession of their respective legacies without an administration of the succession, on the ex parte petition of all of the general and universal legatees, if each of them is either competent or is acting through a qualified legal representative, and each of them accepts the succession, and none of the creditors of the succession has demanded its administration.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3031__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>In such cases, the surviving spouse in community of the testator may be recognized by the court as entitled to the possession of the community property, as provided in Article 3001.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111594</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
